The paper discusses the development and testing of AI-based technologies in a virtual environment, which suggests a strong connection to the cs.AI sub-category. The use of a game engine to simulate critical incidents and data collection by autonomous drones suggests a focus on graphics and visualization, which aligns with the cs.GR sub-category. The mention of autonomous drones also suggests a connection to the cs.RO sub-category, which deals with robotics and control systems. The paper also discusses the identification and gathering of key forensic evidence, which suggests a connection to the cs.CR sub-category, which deals with security and privacy. Finally, the use of simulated Remote Aerial Vehicles (RAVs) to gather images from the environment for the purpose of mapping suggests a connection to the cs.CV sub-category, which deals with computer vision and image processing.
